We may now briefly summarise the arguments in favor of the Summam. Tacitean authorship of the Dialoqus, presented in the preceding pages. It has been shown:

(1) That the testimony of the MSS. is unimpeachable.

(2) That the treatise cannot possibly have been composed after the reign of Titus (79-81).
